item.title: NSW premier won’t castigate feuding MPs
item.description: At least two candidates look set to contest the Liberal preselection for the federal NSW seat of Eden-Monaro after feuding state frontbenchers John Barilaro and Andrew Constance ruled themselves out of the race.

item.title: China demand drives record trade surplus
item.description: A solid growth in mineral exports in March after Chinese factories reopened following the coronavirus shutdown has driven Australia's trade surplus to a record $10.6 billion, in seasonally adjusted terms.

item.title: Prior notice for power outages in Victoria
item.description: Victorians will soon be notified via text message or email of electricity outages before they happen and told if any planned works are cancelled.

item.title: Astronomers discover closest black hole
item.description: Meet your new but shy galactic neighbour: a black hole left over from the death of a fleeting young star.

item.title: Tesla CEO Elon Musk in line for big payday
item.description: Tesla chief executive Elon Musk appears to have hit all the milestones he needed to receive a stock award now worth about $US730 million, a payday that will further pad the eccentric billionaire's vast fortune.

item.title: Pandemic to hasten digital disruption: QBE
item.description: QBE's chief executive says the eventual recovery from COVID-19 will hasten the trend of digital disruption that was underway before the pandemic began.

item.title: ACT students in staged return to school
item.description: Public school students in Canberra will return to their classrooms in stages over the next four weeks after schools shut due to coronavirus.

item.title: US fast food chain’s costly beef with Aust
item.description: For years American fast food giant Wendy's poked fun at Australia and rival US restaurant chains for using Australian beef in their hamburgers.

item.title: Israeli court paves way for govt formation
item.description: Israel's highest court has rejected petitions against another term for right-wing Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and a coalition agreement, paving the way for the formation of a government.

item.title: Virus takes $102b bite of household budget
item.description: Australian households will miss out on $102 billion of income through lost jobs and lower hours because of the coronavirus crisis.
